President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his Administration. Neil Chatterjee of Kentucky is nominated to be a Member of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. He has previously worked as an energy policy advisor to United States Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell and has played a role in the passage of major energy, highway, and farm legislation. Jay Patrick Murray of Virginia is nominated to be the Alternate Representative of the United States of America for Special Political Affairs in the United Nations. He is a retired United States Army Colonel with experience in Iraq, the Balkans, and the United States Embassy Moscow. Robert F. Powelson of Pennsylvania is nominated to be a Member of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. He currently serves as a Commissioner on the Pennsylvania Public Utility Commission and is the President of the National Association of Regulatory Utility Commissioners. Adam J. Sullivan of Iowa is nominated to be Assistant Secretary of Transportation, Government Affairs. He has previous experience in both chambers of Congress and the executive branch, including serving as a Professional Staff Member at the United States Senate Appropriations Subcommittee on Labor, Health and Human Services, and Education.